---
import BaseLayout from '@/layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import LegalLayout from '@/components/legal/LegalLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Privacy Policy — Indval Technologies"
  description="How Indval Technologies collects, uses, and protects your personal data."
  noindex={true}
>
  <LegalLayout title="Privacy Policy" effectiveDate="25 June 2026">

    <h2>1. Who We Are</h2>
    <p>
      This Privacy Policy applies to the website <strong>www.indvaltech.com</strong> and is issued by
      the following legal entities (collectively, "IndvalTech", "we", "our", "us"):
    </p>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Indval Technologies Private Limited</strong> — Nagarbhavi, Bengaluru 560072, Karnataka, India (primary data controller)</li>
      <li><strong>Indval Technologies Sp. z o.o.</strong> — Ul. Piłsudskiego 74/320, 50-020 Wrocław, Poland · KRS 0001238201 · NIP 8971971294 (EU data controller)</li>
      <li><strong>Regent Indval Engineering Services LLC</strong> — 28110 W Harrison Pkwy, Valencia, CA 91355, United States</li>
    </ul>
    <p>
      For enquiries relating to data protection, contact us at
      <a href="mailto:info@indvaltech.com">info@indvaltech.com</a>.
    </p>

    <h2>2. What Data We Collect</h2>

    <h3>Contact form submissions</h3>
    <p>
      Our contact form collects your <strong>full name</strong>, <strong>work email address</strong>,
      and a <strong>technical brief or scope of work</strong>. When you submit the form, your device
      opens your own email client and sends the message directly to
      <a href="mailto:info@indvaltech.com">info@indvaltech.com</a>. We do not operate a server that
      receives or stores this data — it passes through your email provider to ours. No data is
      transmitted to IndvalTech servers via the website.
    </p>

    <h3>Language preference</h3>
    <p>
      If you accept our cookie notice, we store your chosen display language
      (<code>en</code>, <code>de</code>, or <code>pl</code>) in your browser's local storage under
      the key <code>lang</code>. This data never leaves your device and is not transmitted to us.
    </p>

    <h3>Consent record</h3>
    <p>
      We store your cookie-consent decision (<code>accepted</code> or <code>declined</code>) in local
      storage under the key <code>indval_consent</code>. This is strictly necessary to avoid
      repeatedly asking for consent and is not transmitted to us.
    </p>

    <h3>Data we do not collect</h3>
    <p>
      We do not use analytics, advertising networks, tracking pixels, or third-party scripts that
      profile visitors. We do not collect IP addresses, device fingerprints, or behavioural data
      through the website.
    </p>

    <h2>3. How We Use Your Data</h2>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Contact form data</strong> — to respond to your engineering enquiry or request for quotation.</li>
      <li><strong>Language preference</strong> — to display the site in the language you selected.</li>
      <li><strong>Consent record</strong> — to honour your privacy choice on return visits.</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>4. Legal Basis for Processing (GDPR)</h2>
    <p>For visitors from the European Economic Area, our legal bases are:</p>
    <ul>
      <li>
        <strong>Legitimate interests (Art. 6(1)(f) GDPR)</strong> — responding to B2B engineering
        enquiries you initiate via email.
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>Consent (Art. 6(1)(a) GDPR)</strong> — storing language preference in local storage.
        You may withdraw consent at any time by clicking "Cookie Preferences" in the page footer.
      </li>
    </ul>

    <h2>5. Data Sharing and Third-Party Processors</h2>
    <p>
      We do not sell, rent, or trade your personal data. Contact form submissions travel through
      standard email infrastructure (your email provider → our email provider, Zoho Mail / Google
      Workspace). No other third parties receive data collected on this website.
    </p>

    <h2>6. Data Retention</h2>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Email enquiries</strong> — retained in our email system for up to 3 years or until the business relationship concludes, whichever is longer.</li>
      <li><strong>Local storage data</strong> — persists in your browser until you clear site data or browser storage.</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>7. Your Rights</h2>

    <h3>EU / EEA residents (GDPR)</h3>
    <p>
      You have the right to access, rectify, or erase your personal data; to restrict or object to
      processing; and to data portability. You may also lodge a complaint with your local supervisory
      authority. In Poland: <strong>Urząd Ochrony Danych Osobowych (UODO)</strong>,
      <a href="https://uodo.gov.pl" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">uodo.gov.pl</a>.
    </p>

    <h3>California residents (CCPA / CPRA)</h3>
    <p>
      You have the right to know what personal information we collect, the right to delete it, and
      the right to opt out of the sale of personal information. We do not sell personal information.
      To exercise your rights, contact <a href="mailto:info@indvaltech.com">info@indvaltech.com</a>.
    </p>

    <h3>India residents (Digital Personal Data Protection Act 2023)</h3>
    <p>
      You have the right to access information about your personal data, to correct inaccurate data,
      to erasure of data no longer needed, and to grievance redressal. Contact our Grievance Officer
      at <a href="mailto:info@indvaltech.com">info@indvaltech.com</a>.
    </p>

    <h2>8. Exercising Your Rights</h2>
    <p>
      Send your request to <a href="mailto:info@indvaltech.com">info@indvaltech.com</a> with the
      subject line "Data Request". We will respond within 30 days (or sooner as required by
      applicable law).
    </p>

    <h2>9. Changes to This Policy</h2>
    <p>
      We may update this policy from time to time. The effective date above will be revised whenever
      material changes are made. We encourage you to review this page periodically.
    </p>

  </LegalLayout>
</BaseLayout>
